---

## What is it?

Tech Hunt is an online escape room where the rooms are locked by **technical puzzles** ‚ÄĒ binary decoding, hex conversion, ASCII challenges, and coding problems. Every game generates a brand new building layout. No two runs are the same.

Teams of up to 5 players share a map, a chat, and a notepad. One player solves a puzzle ‚ÄĒ everyone advances. The leaderboard rewards speed and efficiency.

**Cipher Mode** ‚ÄĒ for puzzle fans. No code required.  
**Programmer Mode** ‚ÄĒ for developers. Debug, trace, predict.

---

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|-------|------|
| Frontend | React 18 + Vite + TailwindCSS v4 |
| Backend | Node.js + Express + Socket.io |
| Database | PostgreSQL (via Neon) |
| Shared types | TypeScript monorepo (`@techhunt/shared`) |
| Hosting | Vercel (client) ¬∑ Railway (server) |

---

## Getting Started

```bash
# Clone and install (workspaces install everything)
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/techhunt.git
cd techhunt && npm install

# Set up environment variables
cp server/.env.example server/.env
cp client/.env.example client/.env

# Run database migrations
cd server && npm run migrate

# Start both servers from root
npm run dev
```

Then open `http://localhost:5173`.

**Required env vars** ‚ÄĒ `DATABASE_URL`, `JWT_SECRET`, `CORS_ORIGIN` in `server/.env`. See `.env.example` for the full list.

---

## Project Structure

```
techhunt/
‚Ēú‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ shared/       ‚Üź Types, enums, constants, socket event names
‚Ēú‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ server/       ‚Üź Express + Socket.io + generation engine + DB models
‚ĒĒ‚ĒÄ‚ĒÄ client/       ‚Üź React + Vite + TailwindCSS
```

The `shared/` package is the single source of truth ‚ÄĒ imported by both client and server. No type drift, no duplicated constants.

---

## Core Rules (for contributors)

1. **Puzzle answers never leave the server.** All validation is server-side.
2. **REST for persistence. Socket.io for real-time sync.** Never mix their roles.
3. **All data structures support multiplayer** ‚ÄĒ even solo features.
4. **`shared/` owns all types, enums, and socket event name constants.**
5. **`engine/` is pure functions only.** No DB calls, no Express, no side effects.

